    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for my house purchase here in toronto. i'm a bit confused... whats escrow exactly and why do i actually need it for the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a protected section of a bank account held for two or more parties who are engaging in a financial transaction. In a house purchase, the bank holds the buyer's and seller's funds, releasing them only when the agreed-upon closing conditions are met. This safeguards both parties, ensuring the buyer's deposit is safe, and that the seller will not withhold the property until all conditions are met. It helps in preventing fraud and miscommunication. At closing, you'll need to open an escrow account to secure funds before handing over to the seller and facilitating smooth settlement of the property transfer. Most homebuyers don't actively manage the account but should have a third party, such as a title company or another lawyer, handle it for them.",
      "source": "target",
