    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so basically it's just like a neutral middleman holding the cash so nobody gets ripped off? who usually manages the actual money inside the account, like is it the lawyer or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exactly, the escrow account functions as a neutral middleman. In the home buying process, the title company or a lawyer, specifically assigned to handle real estate closings, typically manages the money. In some instances, your real estate agent might have a title company that manages the funds. They ensure that the funds are released according to the seller's disclosures and buyer's payment schedule and that all documents are filed correctly after the closing. They are your financial safeguard during the real estate transaction.",
